This episode of HashiCast highlights Liz Rice from Aqua Security.

Liz Rice works for Aqua Security who build a platform which provides development-to-production lifecycle controls for securing containerized applications.  In addition to her work with Aqua, Liz is very active in the world of technology and has given some fascinating talks at GopherCon, DockerCon and many other conferences around the globe.  She is also the maintainer of Kube-bench and Manifesto.

We chat all things application security, the state of the industry, problems application developers face and some things you can do to help build a more secure workflow.

